01:04:14,545 --> 01:04:15,666
But that's a budget item.

910
01:04:15,706 --> 01:04:20,290
That's money that has to be spent so those fields can get the extra five, six years we need.

911
01:04:20,955 --> 01:04:24,737
But I was going to say that they sit there and just don't get treated at all.

912
01:04:24,777 --> 01:04:25,377
No, no, I didn't say that.

913
01:04:25,417 --> 01:04:26,477
No, they get treated.

914
01:04:26,517 --> 01:04:28,138
I just said we don't do a good job with maintenance.

915
01:04:28,178 --> 01:04:28,879
I know they get treated.

916
01:04:29,179 --> 01:04:31,099
I actually, I was there.

917
01:04:32,100 --> 01:04:32,820
The machine came in.

918
01:04:32,860 --> 01:04:33,801
I know all about it.

919
01:04:33,861 --> 01:04:34,481
And it's been done.

920
01:04:34,501 --> 01:04:35,621
The guy is doing a nice job up there.

921
01:04:35,641 --> 01:04:39,623
In fact, the workers up there, and I know them all, they're all making $12 an hour.

922
01:04:39,643 --> 01:04:40,924
They should be up to $15, by the way.

923
01:04:41,024 --> 01:04:43,085
Madam Vice President, Madam Vice President, you have the floor.

924
01:04:43,105 --> 01:04:45,706
But the deep cleaning they were supposed to do for $10,000 two to four times a year has never been done.

925
01:04:51,676 --> 01:04:52,937
As far as I know, it's never been done.

926
01:04:53,137 --> 01:04:54,158
So it needs to be done.

927
01:04:54,398 --> 01:04:57,580
You can start as soon as the budget, you put a line item in there.

928
01:04:57,700 --> 01:04:59,961
Let's do that so we can get some extra years out of this field.

929
01:04:59,981 --> 01:05:00,862
It's not anybody's fault.

930
01:05:01,102 --> 01:05:02,643
It just slipped through the cracks.

931
01:05:02,663 --> 01:05:04,524
No one saw it.

932
01:05:04,604 --> 01:05:08,666
They were grooming what they were told to do, but no one took the time to do the extra step.

933
01:05:08,706 --> 01:05:09,027
That's all.

934
01:05:09,047 --> 01:05:10,467
And they're trying to get some extra years out of it.

935
01:05:10,487 --> 01:05:10,988
That's all.

936
01:05:11,048 --> 01:05:17,171
If I may amend my resolution just to ask what funding has been used to maintain the fields within the last three years?

937
01:05:18,862 --> 01:05:26,448
It's amended by council vice president current to include a question of what funding has been used.

938
01:05:26,688 --> 01:05:27,708
I believe it's council.

939
01:05:27,728 --> 01:05:28,349
Now you could well be.

940
01:05:28,489 --> 01:05:30,571
I think it's been twice a year with Joe Crowley.

941
01:05:30,591 --> 01:05:35,975
Crowley's purpose has been, has been grooming it doing a deeper sweep, but we need to do, we need to take it that extra step.

942
01:05:35,995 --> 01:05:36,335
That's all.

943
01:05:39,037 --> 01:05:41,218
Um, madam vice president has the floor still.

944
01:05:42,559 --> 01:05:43,100
That's it for now.

945
01:05:43,120 --> 01:05:43,420
Thank you.

946
01:05:44,621 --> 01:05:45,502
Uh, counselor night.

947
01:05:45,942 --> 01:05:46,002
Um,

948
01:05:46,586 --> 01:05:52,411
Mr. Carr was one of the first people, I was here, supporting the cause as a citizen back in, what was it, 2004, 2000?

949
01:05:52,771 --> 01:05:52,411
2000.

950
01:05:52,791 --> 01:05:55,913
2000, 2000, the year 2000.

951
01:05:56,293 --> 01:06:00,637
And if I remember correctly, the fields were opened up in 2002?

952
01:06:00,857 --> 01:06:01,197
Fall of 2000.

953
01:06:02,538 --> 01:06:02,818
Fall of 2000.

954
01:06:02,879 --> 01:06:06,802
The barn was approved in February of 2000.

955
01:06:06,882 --> 01:06:09,303
The fields opened in September of 2000.

956
01:06:10,024 --> 01:06:12,426
So we're at year 16 now, anyway.

957
01:06:12,466 --> 01:06:13,847
So I think the shelf life on the field, no?

958
01:06:16,075 --> 01:06:16,956
2010, excuse me.

959
01:06:16,996 --> 01:06:18,576
Yeah, it was going to say, yeah.

960
01:06:18,677 --> 01:06:20,097
It was like, that doesn't, 2010, February, 2010.

961
01:06:20,137 --> 01:06:20,317
Yeah.

962
01:06:20,437 --> 01:06:24,339
And then we open it now, fall of 2010, excuse me.

963
