I'm off by 10.

964
01:06:25,440 --> 01:06:27,001
So 2008, it went out 2010 and opened.

965
01:06:27,021 --> 01:06:29,282
We're heading into our seventh, we're heading into our seventh year.

966
01:06:29,462 --> 01:06:29,942
Seventh year.

967
01:06:30,203 --> 01:06:30,423
Yes.

968
01:06:30,603 --> 01:06:30,863
Okay.

969
01:06:34,085 --> 01:06:35,425
All right.

970
01:06:35,806 --> 01:06:36,406
Thank you very much.

971
01:06:36,426 --> 01:06:36,726
Thank you.

972
01:06:37,066 --> 01:06:38,267
Councilor Scarpelli.

973
01:06:38,367 --> 01:06:39,427
Just, just to follow up.

974
01:06:39,507 --> 01:06:42,469
I know this is, this is what a part of what I do for a living.

975
01:06:42,909 --> 01:06:44,230
So, um,

976
01:06:45,642 --> 01:06:57,634
To be honest with everyone here, the maintenance of a field, what was true to be a maintenance of a field was the vacuuming two times a year by Joe Crowley and what they do.

977
01:06:59,415 --> 01:07:07,964
I personally met with a company last week that has a true understanding of what you're supposed to do, and they would come in to do all the tests that are needed.

978
01:07:08,404 --> 01:07:19,047
And one test that's very important is a concussion impact test, whether our facilities are safe enough for our kids because of the pellets, what's added, what's not added.

979
01:07:19,447 --> 01:07:28,750
And it's something to the point where there was quoted for us was $6,000 and they would come in and what they would do is the true maintenance where they would suck up all the pellets,

980
01:07:29,570 --> 01:07:35,556
re-sweep the fibers so they're upright again, and then re-enter the pellets.

981
01:07:36,097 --> 01:07:44,605
And then with that, you would get a certified study that would make sure that you are covered by insurance and so on.

982
01:07:44,705 --> 01:07:51,252
So that's something, as we move forward, I know that one of the things we talked about and one of the things Mr. Carr said,

983
01:07:52,213 --> 01:08:04,341
When I talked to some of the school committee members, they're also coming out Monday with a detailed plan of all the facilities and funding and what each facility would cost.

984
01:08:04,802 --> 01:08:11,286
I personally think that we in Somerville, what we charge is $185 per hour flat fee.

985
01:08:11,907 --> 01:08:19,072
And that's something that I would like to see the school committee look at maybe increasing the fee for non-resident programs.

986
01:08:19,592 --> 01:08:34,523
So, the BSSCs, the club soccer programs that make money, that come in and fund that to help pay for maintenance and pay for turf recovery as we move forward.

987
01:08:34,943 --> 01:08:43,330
This is what we're doing and we hope that as Monday's meeting comes out, would spell out a lot of what we're trying to think of.

988
01:08:45,404 --> 01:09:01,156
This is easy, and I point back to a resolution I made last week, this is easy when you have a recreation department that oversees the fields, the maintenance, the budgeting, the rentals, the employees, soup to nuts.

989
01:09:02,197 --> 01:09:08,122
When we have one person doing six jobs, this is where it's difficult.

990
01:09:08,182 --> 01:09:13,206
So it's gonna come time that we should, and I'm anxious to see what we,

991
01:09:13,599 --> 01:09:19,509
have for a recreation plan going forward, but it's going to be interesting to see where we're going to go with this because.

992
01:09:21,172 --> 01:09:29,559
I want us to look outside the box and think maybe sometimes spending a little money is going to save us a lot of money as we move forward.

993
01:09:29,659 --> 01:09:32,321
So again, I appreciate Mr. Carr.

994
01:09:32,341 --> 01:09:33,282
I know everything you've done.

995
01:09:34,042 --> 01:09:41,588
I will tell you what I've been told what's done at Medford High School is something very important to me, many different levels.

996
01:09:41,828 --> 01:09:43,450
I was part of this program when it started.

997
01:09:44,090 --> 01:09:46,912
My son will be playing at the high school in a few years.

998
01:09:47,373 --> 01:09:49,294
It's very important that we do the right thing.

999
01:09:50,744 --> 01:09:55,166
hope that there's safe turf and safe fields for our kids to play on for years to come.

1000
01:09:55,206 --> 01:10:00,908
So I would love to share what I know with the school committee with plans.

1001
01:10:00,968 --> 01:10:06,089
And it's not $10,000, it's $6,000 per field for the whole plan.

1002
01:10:06,590 --> 01:10:15,433
And that's every season coming in, doing two deep cleanings, doing two vacuums that what Crowley does now, and sweeping and adding pellets when needed.

1003
01:10:15,853 --> 01:10:18,554
So it's a pretty intricate system.

1004
01:10:20,067 --> 01:10:20,787
Thank you for listening.

1005
01:10:21,087 --> 01:10:21,927
Thank you, Counselor.

1006
01:10:21,947 --> 01:10:23,288
Chair recognizes Counselor Max.

1007
01:10:24,208 --> 01:10:24,968
Thank you, Mr. President.

1008
01:10:24,988 --> 01:10:27,569
I want to thank Bill Carr Jr.

1009
01:10:27,609 --> 01:10:28,409
for coming up tonight.

1010
01:10:29,609 --> 01:10:37,451
He was one of the biggest advocates that I recall back in the days when the field of dreams was in its infancy.

1011
01:10:38,151 --> 01:10:42,912
And, you know, I just want to say, Mr. President, that we're discussing a bubble top.

1012
01:10:43,773 --> 01:10:48,474
And in my opinion, we should be discussing books in the schools that are 25 years old.

1013
01:10:50,057 --> 01:10:54,000
We should be discussing the fact that teachers don't have proper supplies.

1014
01:10:54,641 --> 01:10:58,904
We should be discussing the deplorable condition of the restrooms at the high school.

1015
01:10:59,324 --> 01:11:06,630
I'd venture to say probably 60 or 70% of the bathrooms in the high school are physically locked because they're in deplorable condition.

1016
01:11:07,931 --> 01:11:09,932
The water fountains don't work throughout the high school.

1017
01:11:09,972 --> 01:11:14,276
And that may be a good thing because of lead pipes that we have throughout this community.

1018
01:11:14,756 --> 01:11:16,737
So that may be a positive thing that they're not working.

1019
01:11:17,278 --> 01:11:18,219
We have a leaky roof.

1020
01:11:19,068 --> 01:11:25,892
I was up there several weeks ago watching my son play a basketball game, and they had to navigate between barrels because the roof was leaking.

1021
01:11:26,653 --> 01:11:28,514
These are the issues we should be discussing.

1022
01:11:28,914 --> 01:11:33,237
And in my opinion, I'm not pro or con of a bubble top.

1023
01:11:33,277 --> 01:11:34,417
I haven't seen the proposal.

1024
01:11:34,858 --> 01:11:46,965
But I could just tell you from firsthand experience, serving as a member of the school committee, that when we had the swimming pool up and running back some years ago, and the lack of resources, and the lack of upkeep on the pool,

1025
01:11:47,384 --> 01:11:54,650
and we rented it out to all the surrounding neighborhood communities to use our Olympic-sized swimming pool, over the years it deteriorated.

1026
01:11:54,990 --> 01:11:59,073
And we got to a point where we couldn't use the swimming pool for I think it was roughly eight years.

1027
01:11:59,613 --> 01:12:02,395
That went unused because of the lack of maintenance.

1028
01:12:02,736 --> 01:12:06,098
It was great to rent it out, and God knows where that rental money went.

1029
01:12:06,438 --> 01:12:08,100
It sure didn't go back into the swimming pool.

1030
01:12:08,600 --> 01:12:09,861
But that's the issue I have.

1031
01:12:10,181 --> 01:12:11,442
You know, rentals sound great.

1032
01:12:11,462 --> 01:12:13,564
Bringing in outside money sounds great.

1033
01:12:14,408 --> 01:12:18,832
You know, we've been renting out the high school every Saturday for the past 25 years.

1034
01:12:19,213 --> 01:12:22,175
There's over 700 people every Saturday.

1035
01:12:22,716 --> 01:12:26,479
I'd ask anyone in the community to go up, and you can't get a pocket spot up at the high school.

1036
01:12:27,300 --> 01:12:30,603
And it's a great program they run up there, the Japanese Language Arts Program.

1037
01:12:31,164 --> 01:12:33,566
And they have complete run of the entire high school.

1038
01:12:34,567 --> 01:12:35,648
However, Mr. President,

1039
01:12:36,207 --> 01:12:50,329
I don't see any benefits over the years that we can say, well, this program has put on a new roof, or this program repaved the parking lot, or this program helped us do X, Y, and Z. I have yet to see any of that, Mr. President.

1040
01:12:50,750 --> 01:12:57,031
And it's great to rent out the high school and our middle school and the pool and the field of dreams, and that's great.

1041
01:12:57,691 --> 01:13:04,892
But without, as Mr. Carr mentioned and Councilor Longo, without the proper maintenance, which this city has a poor track record,

1042
01:13:05,546 --> 01:13:09,591
We're going to be putting good money after bad money after renting these facilities out.

1043
01:13:10,371 --> 01:13:15,537
And I, as one member of this council, I remember the bond funding that needed for the Field of Dreams.

1044
01:13:16,378 --> 01:13:21,424
And I, as one member of this council, Mr. President, rather see the local use.

1045
01:13:22,105 --> 01:13:23,747
Yeah, we might not make as much on it.

1046
01:13:23,767 --> 01:13:24,087
You're right.

1047
01:13:24,486 --> 01:13:31,288
It may not be, but we're not in the business in this community to make money, to rent out fields.

1048
01:13:31,328 --> 01:13:32,829
Let's rent City Hall out.

1049
01:13:33,269 --> 01:13:36,710
I mean, we're not in the business of renting facilities in this community.

1050
01:13:36,990 --> 01:13:38,450
We're not in the rental business.

1051
01:13:39,310 --> 01:13:50,254
I want to make sure the fields are there, the fields are safe, and they're in great user condition for our athletes, for our students, for our intramural teams, and so forth.

1052
01:13:50,554 --> 01:13:54,115
That's what I'm concerned about, not renting it out to these outside

1053
01:13:54,734 --> 01:13:58,657
places that have no affiliation, just want to use it as a space.

1054
01:13:59,278 --> 01:14:03,381
And I don't know, Mr. President, I have a lot of reservations with that.

1055
01:14:03,661 --> 01:14:07,644
You know, the determination is up to the school committee, and good luck to them.

1056
01:14:08,144 --> 01:14:11,567
Apparently, they don't need any money from this council, so they're going off on their own.

1057
01:14:12,267 --> 01:14:13,008
And good luck to them.

1058
01:14:13,068 --> 01:14:15,310
But, you know, let's take a look at the high school.

1059
01:14:16,290 --> 01:14:17,952
Let's get our current needs underway.

1060
01:14:18,372 --> 01:14:22,235
If that high school was ship-shaped, Mr. President, I wouldn't even have made this speech tonight.

1061
01:14:22,861 --> 01:14:30,465
But I can tell you firsthand, having two children at the high school  I don't know when the last time you've been up to high school, but I have two children that go there on a daily basis.

1062
01:14:31,246 --> 01:14:39,890
And when they don't have a restroom to attend, when the bubbler doesn't work, when books they come home with look like they're from ancient Egypt, there's a problem, Mr. President.

1063
01:14:40,251 --> 01:14:43,052
There's a problem with what's going on for the basic necessities.

1064
01:14:43,432 --> 01:14:48,355
And when teachers can't muster together paper and pencil and the basics, there's a concern.

1065
01:14:50,416 --> 01:14:51,857
So, I thank Mr. Carr for coming up.

1066
01:14:52,294 --> 01:14:54,055
And I thank Councilor Longo for putting this on.

1067
01:14:54,475 --> 01:14:59,099
And I think we should all be getting a copy of this RFP or draft of the RFP, whatever it is.

1068
01:14:59,559 --> 01:15:02,901
So we're informed when we get the calls from residents.

1069
01:15:03,522 --> 01:15:04,402
Thank you, Councilor.

1070
01:15:04,702 --> 01:15:06,283
Chair recognizes Councilor Caviello.

1071
01:15:06,403 --> 01:15:07,404
Thank you, Mr. President.

1072
01:15:08,305 --> 01:15:14,089
As we all know, I think maintenance has been the Achilles heel of this whole city over for many years.

1073
01:15:14,989 --> 01:15:18,712
And Councilor Marks is right.

1074
01:15:18,732 --> 01:15:19,692
We rent out the school.

1075
01:15:19,712 --> 01:15:20,493
We rent out everything.

1076
01:15:21,426 --> 01:15:21,966
It's everybody.

