1146
01:21:26,261 --> 01:21:30,063
But I mean, I will say, some people may disagree.

1147
01:21:30,587 --> 01:21:33,189
over time, that has improved a bit.

1148
01:21:33,329 --> 01:21:36,351
I mean, we've actually made some progress in that area.

1149
01:21:36,751 --> 01:21:40,933
For example, filters getting changed on a regular basis, whereas before, there were issues.

1150
01:21:41,013 --> 01:21:44,656
So I mean, preventive maintenance is the key to any project.

1151
01:21:45,196 --> 01:21:47,597
In a project like this, it has to be the key.

1152
01:21:47,978 --> 01:21:49,078
I mean, I remember Field of Dreams.

1153
01:21:49,138 --> 01:21:50,719
It was the first thing I voted on.

1154
01:21:51,540 --> 01:21:56,483
It was the first issue that came before us when we were elected in 2010, was voting for the Field of Dreams.

1155
01:21:57,083 --> 01:21:59,605
I still think today it's a good vote.

1156
01:21:59,705 --> 01:22:00,305
It's a great vote.

1157
01:22:00,861 --> 01:22:06,537
Um, you know, and I think that we have to think about when we think about education, we think of students, we have to think about well rounded students.

1158
01:22:06,959 --> 01:22:07,701
We need to make sure.

1159
01:22:08,125 --> 01:22:12,609
you know, we, we provide, uh, things both inside the classroom and outside the classroom.

1160
01:22:12,969 --> 01:22:14,851
And I, I understand your, you know, about the books.

1161
01:22:15,311 --> 01:22:17,533
We do need to make sure our books are current 25 years.

1162
01:22:17,553 --> 01:22:20,055
I, I, I didn't know we had any of that old.

1163
01:22:20,195 --> 01:22:23,478
I knew we do have some old textbooks, but I didn't think they were that old.

1164
01:22:23,498 --> 01:22:32,266
But, um, and I'd love to know what class we can talk afterwards, but I'd love to know what class has those because we need to get the school committee needs to know that those have to be replaced.

1165
01:22:32,906 --> 01:22:33,587
But, um,

1166
01:22:34,733 --> 01:22:37,415
But, I mean, it's, you know, we want to make sure we have well-rounded students.

1167
01:22:37,575 --> 01:22:46,421
The fields are a great example of how we, our children and our students, can actually use, you know, get physical activity through sports and recreation.

1168
01:22:46,461 --> 01:22:49,683
And it's important that we have, you know, state-of-the-art facilities to do that.

1169
01:22:50,404 --> 01:22:53,146
But for me, you know, it comes down to preventive maintenance.

1170
01:22:53,326 --> 01:23:01,752
And what I'd like to see is, you know, and if I could amend the resolution, is just to receive a business plan from the school committee as to what they're going to do as far as

1171
01:23:02,223 --> 01:23:07,870
you know, how much is going to be charged, the plans to rent it out, I mean, how much is being set aside for preventive maintenance.

1172
01:23:08,370 --> 01:23:11,554
So if we could add that to the resolution, I'd greatly appreciate it.

1173
01:23:13,136 --> 01:23:13,296
Add.

1174
01:23:15,118 --> 01:23:22,727
If we get the school committee could give us the proposed business plan for the fields with regard to, um, you know,

1175
01:23:23,208 --> 01:23:27,853
with your charging the cost, how much is going back to preventive maintenance, basically the plan.

1176
01:23:27,893 --> 01:23:28,554
What's the plan?

1177
01:23:28,634 --> 01:23:34,981
I mean, I know we talked a little bit about the hours, you know, who's gonna be renting it out if possible.

1178
01:23:35,041 --> 01:23:39,005
I mean, that type of thing, the type of programming that's gonna be offered.

1179
01:23:39,366 --> 01:23:39,706
Thank you.

